) housed in 
<collectionCode box="[341,401,706,729]" country="Indonesia" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/b9gz-izvg" name="Museum Zoologicum Bogoriense" pageId="5" pageNumber="220">MZB</collectionCode>
(47006).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="220" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,561,1990]" pageId="5" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,741,766]" pageId="5" pageNumber="220">Description.</emphasis>
Shell small, slightly exceeding 
<quantity box="[740,826,742,766]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="220" unit="mm" value="20.0">20 mm</quantity>
in length, relatively robust, equivalve, moderately inflated. Shape slightly elongate, ovate-subquadrate, moderately inequilateral, well rounded anteriorly, poorly to moderately convex ventrally, barely truncate posteriorly. Umbo small, protruding, prosogyrate. Lunule small, slightly concave; escutcheon markedly elongate, deeply sunken. Ligament external, elongate, opisthodetic.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,561,1990]" pageId="5" pageNumber="220">Radial sculpture consisting of 24–26 poorly convex ribs. Radial interspaces narrow, shallow, poorly impressed ventrally. Growth striae distinct, closely set, crossing radial ribs and interspaces, producing a fine, irregular and decussate pattern. Commarginal sculpture mainly lamellose near ventral margin. Posterior slope distinct, with about five, notably finer ribs. Early sculpture consisting of beaded radial ribs, with slightly deeper and larger interspaces.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,561,1990]" pageId="5" pageNumber="220">Hinge plate moderately robust, slightly arched. Right hinge with three cardinal teeth: anterior tooth small, poorly developed; central tooth robust, triangular, elongate, strongly oblique; posterior tooth elongate, medially grooved, parallel to posterior-dorsal margin. Left hinge with two cardinal teeth: anterior tooth smaller, somewhat triangular, slightly oblique; posterior tooth larger, elongate, parallel to posterior-dorsal margin. Lateral dentition only represented by a small, tubercle-shaped anterior lateral tooth on both valves.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,561,1990]" pageId="5" pageNumber="220">Inner margin coarsely crenulate anteriorly and ventrally, more finely posteriorly. Pallial line entire, moderately convex. Anterior adductor muscle scar slightly larger, reniform; posterior scar roughly triangular; both well distinct.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1233,1353,1378]" pageId="5" pageNumber="220" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,561,1990]" box="[199,1233,1353,1378]" pageId="5" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1353,1378]" pageId="5" pageNumber="220">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="de Stefani" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[359,594,1353,1378]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Akardita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditida" pageId="5" pageNumber="220" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="subrevoluta">
<emphasis box="[359,594,1353,1378]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="220">Akardita subrevoluta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known from the lower Pliocene of northern 
<collectingCountry box="[1175,1228,1353,1378]" name="Italy" pageId="5" pageNumber="220">Italy</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="220" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,561,1990]" pageId="5" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1389,1414]" pageId="5" pageNumber="220">Remarks.</emphasis>
The present species was first reported as 
<taxonomicName authority="Seguenza, 1877" authorityName="Seguenza" authorityYear="1877" box="[803,1184,1389,1414]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Cardita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditida" pageId="5" pageNumber="220" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="revoluta">
<emphasis box="[803,992,1389,1414]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="220">Cardita revoluta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[1001,1184,1390,1414]" pageId="5" pageNumber="220" refId="ref10227" refString="Seguenza, G. (1877) Studi stratigrafici sulla formazione pliocenica dell'Italia meridionale. Bullettino del Reale Comitato Geologico d'Italia, 8, 7 - 17." type="journal article">Seguenza, 1877</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from the Pliocene of Siena by de 
<bibRefCitation box="[294,610,1425,1450]" pageId="5" pageNumber="220" refId="ref8033" refString="de Stefani, C. &amp; Pantanelli, D. (1878) Molluschi pliocenici dei dintorni di Siena. Bullettino della Societa Malacologica Italiana, 4, 1 - 215." type="journal article">Stefani &amp; Pantanelli (1878)</bibRefCitation>
, who added a description. Ten years later, de 
<bibRefCitation pageId="5" pageNumber="220" refId="ref8005" refString="de Stefani, C. (1888) Iconografia dei nuovi molluschi pliocenici d'intorno Siena. Bullettino della Societa Malacologica Italiana, 13, 209 - 235." type="journal article">Stefani (1888: 189, pl. 10, figs 11–13)</bibRefCitation>
noted some differences from Seguenza's species and described it as new, re-proposing the early description: &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="220">Testa cordata, subquadrata; latus anticum rotundatum, latus posticum obtuse-angulatum, margo pallearis convexiusculus: costae longitudinales 24–26 magnae, convexae; intervallis brevissimis separatae; transverse, praecipue ad umbones, rugosae: lunula antica parva, parum profunda: umbones recurvi obtusi: margo pallearis profunde crenatus; dens cardinalis in utraque valva brevis, in valva sinistra solidior; dentes laterales tenues, breves</emphasis>
&quot; (Shell heart-shaped, subquadrate; anterior margin convex, posterior margin obtusely angulate, ventral margin poorly convex: 24 
<emphasis box="[571,585,1678,1701]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="220">–</emphasis>
26 radial ribs, wide, convex; separated by very narrow interspaces; commarginally rugose, especially near umbo: lunule anterior, small, slightly deep: umbos incurved, obtuse: ventral margin deeply crenulated; cardinal teeth in both valves short, stronger in left valve; lateral teeth weak, short).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,561,1990]" pageId="5" pageNumber="220">
The valve illustrated by de 
<bibRefCitation box="[521,685,1785,1810]" pageId="5" pageNumber="220" refId="ref8005" refString="de Stefani, C. (1888) Iconografia dei nuovi molluschi pliocenici d'intorno Siena. Bullettino della Societa Malacologica Italiana, 13, 209 - 235." type="journal article">Stefani (1888)</bibRefCitation>
(
<figureCitation box="[703,795,1785,1810]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,249,1578,1600]" captionTargetBox="[173,1427,193,1568]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[173,1427,193,1568]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Akardita subrevoluta (de Stefani, 1888). A–C. LV, Tavernelle (Siena), Italy, lower Pliocene (MZB 47006). D–F. RV, Tavernelle(Siena), Italy, lowerPliocene (MZB 47006).G–I.LV,Tavernelle (Siena), Italy, lowerPliocene (MZB 47006).J. RV, Tavernelle(Siena), Italy, lower Pliocene (MZB 47006). K. Original illustration, after de Stefani (1888: pl. 10, figs 11–13). Scale bars:10 mm (A, B, D, E, G, H, J), 4 mm (C, F, I)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1175460/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="220">Fig. 3K</figureCitation>
) appears more elongate and triangular than the present material, but the size reported in the description (
<quantity box="[748,855,1821,1846]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.65" pageId="5" pageNumber="220" unit="mm" value="16.5">16.5 mm</quantity>
in length, 16.0 mm in height) points to a more equidimensional shape, in agreement with the morphometric trend recorded in the study material (
<figureCitation box="[1242,1332,1857,1882]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,249,1168,1190]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,604,1134]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,591,1146]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Akardita subrevoluta (de Stefani, 1888). A. Scatter plot H vs L (64 valves from Tavernelle) Open circle indicates the size in the original description.B. Scatter plot and least square regression of L/H vs L." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1175462/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="220">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). Growth is mostly isometric, with only a slight increase in elongation with growth, as indicated by a low correlation coefficient (~ 0.5) of L/H vs L (
<figureCitation box="[536,629,1929,1954]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,249,1168,1190]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,604,1134]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,591,1146]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Akardita subrevoluta (de Stefani, 1888). A. Scatter plot H vs L (64 valves from Tavernelle) Open circle indicates the size in the original description.B. Scatter plot and least square regression of L/H vs L." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1175462/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="220">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
). The maximum size is 
<quantity box="[918,1022,1930,1954]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.32" pageId="5" pageNumber="220" unit="mm" value="23.2">23.2 mm</quantity>
in length. Width is 
<quantity box="[1264,1403,1929,1954]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.9" metricValueMax="7.5" metricValueMin="6.3" pageId="5" pageNumber="220" unit="mm" value="6.9" valueMax="7.5" valueMin="6.3">
6.3 
<emphasis box="[1299,1313,1930,1953]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="220">–</emphasis>
7.5 mm
</quantity>
in 19.0 
<emphasis box="[200,214,1966,1989]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="220">–</emphasis>
21.0 mm long valves.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
